---
/**
 * Guided walk — Chapter 6 of 6: "Why you had to dig for this", and the close.
 * The withholding stack (annotated layout): seven lawful-looking layers, the
 * clauses [verified], the "engineered system" reading flagged as argument. Folds
 * in the thesis coda — the thin record, reassembled — and the end-of-walk exits.
 */
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import PathWayfinding from "../../components/PathWayfinding.astro";
import RecordTeardown from "../../components/RecordTeardown.astro";
import WithholdingStack from "../../components/WithholdingStack.astro";
import { OPACITY_TEARDOWN } from "../../lib/teardowns";
import { chapterByStep, WALK_INDEX_HREF, WALK_TOTAL, walkHref } from "../../lib/walk";
import { withBase } from "../../lib/site";

const STEP = 6;
const prev = chapterByStep(STEP - 1);
---

<Base
  title="Why you had to dig for this — Chapter 5"
  section="site"
  description="None of this was meant to be easy to see: a stack of lawful-looking layers keeps the deal's substance non-public. Yet the thin record, reassembled, still tells the story."
>
  <div class="walk-chapter-page">
    <PathWayfinding step={STEP} />

    <div class="walk-chapter-eyebrow">Chapter {STEP} of {WALK_TOTAL} · the guided walk</div>
    <h1 class="walk-chapter-h1">Why you had to dig for this</h1>

    <div class="walk-prose">
      <p>
        By now a fair question: if all of this is public record, why did it take a
        walk to assemble it? Because none of it was meant to be easy to see. The
        withholding here is not one refusal — it's an architecture, layered along
        the records lifecycle, and each layer is individually lawful-looking.
        Open each layer below to read the operative clause and the document it
        lives in.
      </p>
    </div>

    <WithholdingStack />

    <div class="walk-prose">
      <p>
        One record consolidates the whole architecture — the withholding map. Here
        it is as a teardown, with the deciding analysis (item 4) still locked.
      </p>
    </div>

    <RecordTeardown record={OPACITY_TEARDOWN} layout="annotated" />

    <div class="walk-prose">
      <p>
        Hold the line one more time. Every clause and statute above is read from a
        committed document — that part is <code>[verified]</code>. Calling the whole
        an <em>engineered system</em> is argument, and the record says so itself.
        The other distinction worth carrying: “we have no records” is not the same
        as “we won't produce these records.” When items 5–15 were
        <em>deferred</em> as if held elsewhere, the resolutions authorizing them
        were sitting in the Board's own minutes — which means the records exist
        where the request was directed. That gap is a fight you can win.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="callout walk-takeaway">
      <p class="callout-title">What you can read anywhere now</p>
      <p>
        A <strong>statutory exemption</strong> — ask who it protects, on what
        basis, and for how long (R.C. 149.433 shields “infrastructure records” for
        25 years; R.C. 4582.58 keeps developer data out of “record” status
        entirely). And the difference between <strong>“no records”</strong> and
        <strong>“records not produced”</strong> — the second is contestable, and
        the place to look is whoever the deciding act actually went through.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="walk-coda">
      <div class="walk-coda-kicker">The end of the walk</div>
      <h2>The thin record, reassembled</h2>
      <p>
        Six chapters, six records, one method: take a source, read it into
        structured data, say plainly what it means, and leave a path back to the
        proof. The deal was built to be hard to see — and yet, document by
        document, it reassembles. That reassembly, done in the open with provenance
        on every figure, is the whole point.
      </p>
      <p>Now it's yours. Pick any figure and follow its citation to the source.</p>
      <div class="walk-coda-cta">
        <a class="btn" href={withBase("/site/")}>Browse the full archive →</a>
        <a class="walk-cta-secondary" href={withBase("/submit")}>or submit a correction or tip</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <nav class="walk-nav" aria-label="Chapter navigation">
      {
        prev?.live ? (
          <a class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-prev" href={walkHref(prev.slug)}>← {prev.step}. {prev.title}</a>
        ) : (
          <span></span>
        )
      }
      <a class="walk-nav-leave" href={WALK_INDEX_HREF}>All chapters</a>
      <a class="walk-nav-link walk-nav-next" href={withBase("/start")}>↺ Start the walk over</a>
    </nav>
  </div>
</Base>
